      "message": "This should be ready for review, although I will need to suppress some chrome unit tests that are failing exact pixel tests. I survey of our gold differences suggests the changes in vertex count is visually fine, with the most impact around curves approaching a circle. The complexclip2_rrect_bw\nresults that show drop-outs are caused by an earlier CL that hasn\u0027t been triaged yet, while this one just changes how the round-rect corners are rasterized.\n\nRegarding the chrome unit tests, the changes appear benign and just need simple updates to the expected images. The exception is the OopPathPixelTest/Basic, where the expected image has a poor quality circle drawn and the new actual has a nicer circle (likely because of an increased vertex count). What I don\u0027t yet understand is why the expected image (from the legacy gpu-raster path in chrome) would make a different path renderer decision than oop-r. At the very least, I don\u0027t think it indicates a bug in this CL. \n\nI can either suppress that OopPathPixelTest at the same time as the others needing rebaselines, or try and understand what\u0027s going on before this one lands.",
